    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of pine tree native to the southeastern United States, from Texas to Florida and Delaware. It grows to 30-35 m (98-115 feet) tall. The needles usually fall only every two years, giving the species an evergreen character. The word "loblolly" refers to a low wet place, although the trees grow in other habitats as well.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
